Andrey Aleksandrovich Gershun (Russian: Андре́й Алекса́ндрович Ге́ршун, 22 October 1903 – 6 December 1952) was a Soviet physicist known for his work in photometry and optics, and was one of the founders of Vavilov State Optical Institute Hydrooptics Science School.

In 1920 he entered the Physics Department of Peterburg State University and graduated in 1924. He then took a position in the State Optical Institute Photometric Laboratory under the direction of Professor S. O. Mayzel'.

Honors
Stalin Prize (1942, 29.10.1949)
Order of the Red Star (1942)
Order of the Badge of Honour (1945)
Order of the Red Banner of Labour (29.10.1949)

