Zehnder studied mathematics and physics at ETH Zurich from 1960 to 1965, where he also did his Ph.D. in theoretical physics... He had appointments at the University of Bochum from 1976 to 1986; at the University of Aix-la-Chapelle during the academic year 1987–88... From 1988, he had a chair at ETH Zurich, where he became emeritus in 2006. He was plenary speaker at the International Congress of Mathematicians (ICM) in 1986... In 2012 he became a fellow of the American Mathematical Society. In 2021 he was elected a member of the Academia Europaea.

